# React & Next.js

Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next.js code — APIs may differ from training data.

For performance, data fetching, and bundle optimization, read `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/SKILL.md` on demand.

## Components

- Arrow functions only; use `FC<ComponentNameProps>` with `import type { FC } from "react"`
- Props interface named `ComponentNameProps`; prefer **named exports** (`export const Button`)
- Filenames are kebab-case (see `file-naming` rule); component exports stay PascalCase
- Each component folder has an `index.ts` barrel; import from the folder path (e.g. `@/components/ui/button`), not the implementation file

```tsx
// ui/button/index.ts
export { Button, type ButtonProps, type ButtonVariant } from "./button";

// elsewhere
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
```
- Optional `classNames` prop for style extension; styling rules in `styling.mdc`

```tsx
import type { FC } from "react";

export interface SiteHeaderProps {
  variant?: "light" | "dark";
  classNames?: string;
}

export const SiteHeader: FC<SiteHeaderProps> = ({ variant = "light", classNames }) => (
  /* ... */
);
```

## Server vs client

- Default to Server Components
- Add `'use client'` at top of file only for interactivity, browser APIs, or hooks
- Extract interactive parts into small client components; compose with server parents
- Do not use Next.js global `error.tsx` boundaries — handle errors at component level

## Route files

Colocate feature code under `app/` with underscore prefixes (`_components/`, `_lib/`) so folders are not routes.

| File | Component name | Props type |
|------|----------------|------------|
| `page.tsx` | `Page` | `PageProps<'/route'>` |
| `layout.tsx` | `Layout` | `LayoutProps<'/route'>` |
| `not-found.tsx` | `NotFound` | — |
| `forbidden.tsx` | `Forbidden` | — |
| `unauthorised.tsx` | `Unauthorised` | — |

```tsx
import type { FC } from "react";

const Page: FC<PageProps<"/route-path">> = async ({ params, searchParams }) => {
  /* ... */
};

export default Page;
```

Colocate Server Actions in `actions.ts` within the feature directory. Authenticate inside each action.

## Environment variables

Validate `process.env` with Zod in a central `src/env.ts`; use `parse` at startup. Never use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` — all env vars are server-side. Import `env`, not `process.env`.

## Middleware

Next.js 16 uses `src/proxy.tsx` (not `middleware.ts`). Export a default async function receiving `NextRequest`.

## Metadata

- Static: export `metadata` from `layout.tsx` or `page.tsx`
- Dynamic: export async `generateMetadata`
- Structured data: JSON-LD via `<script type="application/ld+json">`

## Code layout

- **Shared:** `src/components/`, `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`
- **Feature-specific:** colocated under `src/app/<feature>/` with `_` prefixes
- Hooks: `use-hook-name.ts` in `src/hooks/`

## Suspense

Wrap async server components in `<Suspense fallback={...}>` at route or section boundaries — not around the entire page when only part of the tree needs data.
